questions.context: Lucas decided to skip breakfast one morning, despite knowing that it would make him feel tired during the day. However, to his surprise, he didn't feel tired at all.
questions.question: Does this imply that lucas skipped breakfast?

questions.context: Kevin enjoys spending his leisure time either playing cricket outside or playing chess inside. Whenever he decides to play cricket outside, his friends always join him, adding to the fun. Similarly, when he chooses to play chess inside, his sister eagerly participates in the game. Today, Kevin was unsure about his preferred activity and found himself torn between the two options. However, he knew that at least one of the following scenarios would unfold: either he would play cricket outside, or he would indulge in a game of chess indoors. The uncertainty of the situation left Kevin excited and curious about how the day would unfold.
questions.question: Can we say at least one of the following must always be true? (a) his friends will join him and (b) his sister will join him
